
 Symfony Installer (1.1.7)
 =========================

 This is the official installer to start new projects based on the
 Symfony full-stack framework.

 To create a new project called [32mblog[39m in the current directory using
 the [32mlatest stable version[39m of Symfony, execute the following command:

   [33mSymfony new blog[39m

 Create a project based on the [32mSymfony Long Term Support version[39m (LTS):

   [33mSymfony new blog lts[39m

 Create a project based on a [32mspecific Symfony branch[39m:

   [33mSymfony new blog 2.3[39m

 Create a project based on a [32mspecific Symfony version[39m:

   [33mSymfony new blog 2.5.6[39m

 Create a [32mdemo application[39m to learn how a Symfony application works:

   [33mSymfony demo[39m

 Updating the Symfony Installer
 ------------------------------

 New versions of the Symfony Installer are released regularly. To [32mupdate your
 installer[39m version, execute the following command:

   [33mSymfony self-update[39m

